{"key":"post-13534452","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13534452</id>\n<content>Low level ambient light will stimulate slightly faster colonization because mycelium derives energy from light.&amp;nbsp; There is evidence that very bright light, such as used for pinning will actually slow down colonization.&amp;nbsp; However, normal ambient room light from day one is actually a good thing.&amp;nbsp; Just don't put your colonizing spawn in front of a window in direct sunlight.&amp;nbsp; The old advice to 'colonize in total darkness' is bogus and has been proved incorrect over many tens of thousands of grows.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13534890</next>\n<prev>13534431</prev>\n<first>13533905</first>\n<last>13536875</last>\n<when>1290617536</when>\n<utime>11/24/10 06:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}